==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Orphan
<hw>Or"phan</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>orphanus</ets>, Gr. <?/, akin to L. <ets>orbus</ets>. Cf.
<er>Orb</er> a blank window.]</ety> <def>A child bereaved of both father
and mother; sometimes, also, a child who has but one parent
living.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Orphans' court</b></col> <fld>(Law)</fld>, <cd>a court in
some of the States of the Union, having jurisdiction over the estates
and persons of orphans or other wards.</cd>
<rj><au>Bouvier.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Orphan</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Orphan
<hw>Or"phan</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Bereaved of parents, or (sometimes)
of one parent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Orphan</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Orphan
<hw>Or"phan</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Orphaned</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Orphaning</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To cause to become an orphan;
to deprive of parents.</def> <rj><au>Young.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Orphanage</ent>⟦br⟧
